  "summary": "Reverse shell backdoor to hardcoded IP",
  "details": "The package's main module (index.js lines 5-9) exports a function that opens a TCP connection to 223.229.156.10:5513 and pipes a spawned shell's stdin/stdout/stderr through that socket — a classic interactive reverse shell. Any environment that loads this package and invokes the exported function hands the operator of that IP a fully interactive shell on the host. The package's own package.json description self-identifies as malware (\"this has a malware and it is only for testing purpose\"), and the package name resembles a generic logging/random-string utility, consistent with a deliberate malicious publish.",
